                "State University"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Liquid hydrogen target located at the target position",
                "of the S800. The liquid hydrogen was contained by a",
                "cylindrical aluminum target cell, with a 125 mu-m",
                "Kapton entrance and exit windows. The nominal target",
                "thickness was 30 mm. The temperature and the pressure",
                "of the target cell were 17.0 K and 880 Torr.",
                "Variations of target thickness caused by pressure",
                "difference across Kapton entrance and exit windows",
                "were taken into account. Areal density of the target",
                "was (240+-2) mg/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "IOCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Outgoing beam particles were identified by",
                "energy loss in the S800 ionization chamber and time",
                "of flight."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma rays emitted by the reaction products",
                "were detected by eight modules of the GRETINA",
                "gamma-ray tracking array, centered on the target.",
                "Eight modules housing four 36-fold segmented",
                "high-purity germanium crystals were installed on one",
                "of the GRETINA mounting hemispheres to accommodate",
                "the target. Two modules were centered at 58deg, four",
                "at 90deg, and two at 122deg with respect to the beam",
                "axis."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Particles in the secondary beam as well as",
                "reaction products were identified using time of flight."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "KINDT"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The secondary beams 42,44S and 41,43P were",
                "produced by fragmentation of a 140 MeV/nucleon 48Ca",
                "primary beam in a 1222 mg/cm2 9Be production target",
                "and separated by the A1900 fragment separator. Two",
                "magnet settings of the A1900 were used with momentum",
                "acceptance of 2%. Aluminium wedge was used to",
                "separate secondary beams by Z. The secondary beams",
                "were momentum analysed by S800 spectrograph.",
                "Particles were identified by time of flight using",
                "scintillation detectors in A1900 focal plane and",
                "object and focal plane of S800 spectrograph."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
